Title : Factoria d'Arts Escèniques (Banyoles)
Text : '''Factoria d’Arts Escèniques''' is a cultural building focused in teaching, producing and playing performing arts. It is located in Baldiri Reixach, 403 de [[Banyoles]], [[Pla de l'Estany]]. The building received the official visit of the Minister of Culture, [[Ángeles González-Sinde Reig|González-Sinde]] in October 2010 and inaugurated its first play the 27 March 2011<ref name="Una «Operetta» estrena la Factoria d'Arts Escèniques de Banyoles">{{cite web |url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/cultura/2011/03/28/operetta-estrena-factoria-darts-esceniques-banyoles/475485.html |title=Una "Operetta" estrena la Factoria d'Arts Escèniques de Banyoles |language=catalan|editor=Diari de Girona |date= 28 March 2011}}</ref> but it wasn't officially opened since 20 April 2011.

==Aula de Teatre==
Aula de Teatre is a teaching centre promoted by the Culture Area of Ajuntament de Banyoles. Factoria d'Arts Escèniques is its venue since 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.radiobanyoles.cat/noticia.php?id=6156 |title=L’Aula de Teatre puja a l’escenari per mostrar el treball fet pels alumnes durant el curs |language=catalan |editor=Radio Banyoles |date=28 May 2010}}</ref> Several theatre companies have emerged from Aula de Teatre such as Cor de Teatre, Pocapuc Teatre, Kafkiana and [[El Vol del Pollastre]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elpuntavui.cat/ma/article/5-cultura/19-cultura/499960-classes-gratuites-per-a-joves-dema-a-laula-de-teatre.html |title=Classes gratuïtes per a joves, demà a l'Aula de Teatre |language=catalan|editor=El Punt |date=27 January 2012}}</ref>

